00:38:51.830 --> 00:38:56.750
with lawyers for clients who
live in rural communities and is

00:38:56.750 --> 00:39:01.140
that something that the ABA
is looking at promoting?

00:39:01.140 --> 00:39:03.690
&gt;&gt; Hilarie Bass: So,
one of the focuses

00:39:03.690 --> 00:39:06.010
of our pro bono efforts
this year,

00:39:06.010 --> 00:39:08.790
is providing legal
assistance to homeless youth.

00:39:08.790 --> 00:39:11.630
There are over a million
children in our country

00:39:11.630 --> 00:39:15.430
that live on the street or couch
surf, but don't have a home

00:39:15.430 --> 00:39:18.470
to go to at night and one of
the things we've been focusing

00:39:18.470 --> 00:39:22.100
on is trying to get our
associations, law firms,

00:39:22.100 --> 00:39:25.230
in-house groups to pair
with homeless shelters

00:39:25.230 --> 00:39:28.390
in their community to be
available whether by phone

00:39:28.390 --> 00:39:33.610
