We will help people
do their own research.

00:49:19.330 --> 00:49:22.860
We will help them find
the materials they need,

00:49:22.860 --> 00:49:25.870
but we cannot provide
legal advice.

00:49:25.870 --> 00:49:28.340
We are not practicing attorneys.

00:49:28.340 --> 00:49:31.410
Over to you.

00:49:31.410 --> 00:49:33.520
&gt;&gt; Hilarie Bass: Well, I
there's certainly a lot

00:49:33.520 --> 00:49:36.660
that whether it's the Law
Library of Congress or libraries

00:49:36.660 --> 00:49:41.290
in general, can provide
as far as capabilities.

00:49:41.290 --> 00:49:45.750
One of the things that I would
like to see in every courthouse,

00:49:45.750 --> 00:49:50.280
is some kind of ombudsman
that assists people

00:49:50.280 --> 00:49:54.420
who are there pro hac,
meaning on their own,

00:49:54.420 --> 00:49:57.740
to basically say this is where
you go for this and this is

00:49:57.740 --> 00:49:59.990
where what you do
for that, as well as,

00:49:59.990 --> 00:50:03.310
a kiosk where every state form

00:50:03.310 --> 00:50:06.170
for the basic filings
would be available.

00:50:06.170 --> 00:50:11.020
I mean, for example, uncontested
dissolution of a marriage

00:50:11.020 --> 00:50:13.380
without children,
it's a simple form.

00:50:13.380 --> 00:50:16.290
Why can't there be a
kiosk in every courthouse

00:50:16.290 --> 00:50:19.840
that has the state recognized
form you just type in your name

00:50:19.840 --> 00:50:23.290
and it puts it out and
triplicate and you're done.

00:50:23.290 --> 00:50:24.590
They say, "Oh and by the way,

00:50:24.590 --> 00:50:26.930
this gets filed in
the room 212."

00:50:26.930 --> 00:50:30.190
Why shouldn't we make that
available to our citizens

00:50:30.190 --> 00:50:34.230
who are paying the taxes to
keep the building in place?

00:50:34.230 --> 00:50:36.910
Why don't we create
the opportunity

00:50:36.910 --> 00:50:40.240
for online dispute resolution?

00:50:40.240 --> 00:50:42.890
I had hoped this year and it
doesn't look like it's going

00:50:42.890 --> 00:50:46.290
to happen, that the ABA
come up with a pilot project

00:50:46.290 --> 00:50:47.980
for small claims court.

00:50:47.980 --> 00:50:50.080
Right now, if you're
a low-income person

00:50:50.080 --> 00:50:54.180
and you have let's say it's
a car repair for 800 dollars

00:50:54.180 --> 00:50:56.780
and the repairman runs
off with your money,

00:50:56.780 --> 00:50:58.800
that's a critical
amount of money to you

00:50:58.800 --> 00:51:00.100
and you have no choice

00:51:00.100 --> 00:51:03.310
but to file a small
claims claim, filing.

00:51:03.310 --> 00:51:07.060
Our current system requires
that person to take a day off

00:51:07.060 --> 00:51:10.840
of work, get on a
cross town bus,

00:51:10.840 --> 00:51:14.210
travel for an hour-and-a-half,
wait around for 2 hours

00:51:14.210 --> 00:51:17.880
to be called, be given 5 minutes
with the judge to be told go

00:51:17.880 --> 00:51:19.770
in other room and
try and resolve this.

00:51:19.770 --> 00:51:21.320
If you don't resolve
it, you come back

00:51:21.320 --> 00:51:24.520
and are told well we'll give
you a trial date, 6 weeks out,

00:51:24.520 --> 00:51:27.610
where you, again, take the
day off of work, again,

00:51:27.610 --> 00:51:30.290
why would we have
to do any of that?

00:51:30.290 --> 00:51:32.880
Why can't we have people dictate

00:51:32.880 --> 00:51:35.690
into their Smart phone
what they're claim is,

00:51:35.690 --> 00:51:38.360
have a dedicated email
address where it goes directly

00:51:38.360 --> 00:51:41.020
to the court, obviously
we have to figure

00:51:41.020 --> 00:51:44.760
out how we serve the defendant,
but you can have a judge

00:51:44.760 --> 00:51:48.180
on Skype with 2 people
on Face Time

00:51:48.180 --> 00:51:53.380
and resolve the whole dispute
within a matter of minutes.

00:51:53.380 --> 00:51:58.560
And I believe, that if we have
80% of our population not able

00:51:58.560 --> 00:52:00.970
to access our court system,

00:52:00.970 --> 00:52:04.630
there are so many things we
can do to make them believe

00:52:04.630 --> 00:52:07.680
that the courthouse doors are
open to them, because again,

00:52:07.680 --> 00:52:10.220
when you get to the issue
of having confidence

00:52:10.220 --> 00:52:13.260
in our democracy,
if the vast majority

00:52:13.260 --> 00:52:16.630
of our population does not
believe they can access the

00:52:16.630 --> 00:52:20.930
courts, that impacts their
view of our whole democracy

00:52:20.930 --> 00:52:23.390
because they believe
it doesn't serve them.

00:52:23.390 --> 00:52:28.130
It only serves the other
people and that's not healthy.

00:52:28.130 --> 00:52:30.310
So, we've got to figure
out a way to ensure

00:52:30.310 --> 00:52:33.590
that everybody perceives
that there are ways

00:52:33.590 --> 00:52:39.090
to access the courts to
help solve their problems.

