because we'll do that
by the end of the year,

00:54:59.610 --> 00:55:04.220
but one of the top things
we hear is women complain

00:55:04.220 --> 00:55:07.210
about something called
"success fatigue",

00:55:07.210 --> 00:55:09.770
and this is basically
the idea that women

00:55:09.770 --> 00:55:12.810
and minority lawyers
perceive that they have

00:55:12.810 --> 00:55:15.150
to do everything just
a little bit better

00:55:15.150 --> 00:55:18.260
than their white male
colleagues to get the same level

00:55:18.260 --> 00:55:21.850
of recognition, and
initially that's a bargain

00:55:21.850 --> 00:55:25.120
that we all make because we want
to prove ourselves and we want

00:55:25.120 --> 00:55:29.250
to reach that partnership
level, and be successful,

00:55:29.250 --> 00:55:34.850
but at some point, women tell
us it's just very fatiguing

00:55:34.850 --> 00:55:38.570
and at 25 years in, they
finally say, "You know what?

00:55:38.570 --> 00:55:41.080
I don't want to do this anymore.

00:55:41.080 --> 00:55:42.380
It's just too hard.

00:55:42.380 --> 00:55:44.740
It's just too inherently
unfair."

00:55:44.740 --> 00:55:47.030
So, that's something
we hear a lot about.

00:55:47.030 --> 00:55:52.480
Implicit bias continues to
be a major issue not just

00:55:52.480 --> 00:55:55.940
in the legal profession, but in
industry in general at a time

00:55:55.940 --> 00:55:59.930
when we're all trying
to diversify industry,

00:55:59.930 --> 00:56:02.940
legal professions,
boards; what we know is

00:56:02.940 --> 00:56:05.770
that people feel most
comfortable with people

00:56:05.770 --> 00:56:08.510
who look and act like they do.

00:56:08.510 --> 00:56:13.130
And so, the assumption that were
objective in our analysis just

00:56:13.130 --> 00:56:17.070
because we say, "we're
objective", what we know is

00:56:17.070 --> 00:56:22.850
that bias infiltrates all
of us, women, men, all of us

00:56:22.850 --> 00:56:27.960
and it does affect how we
interact with people and,

00:56:27.960 --> 00:56:29.780
you know, there have been
all kinds of studies done.

