My favorite is the one with the
orchestras where the maestros

00:56:34.060 --> 00:56:37.660
in response to a class
action by 5 top orchestras

00:56:37.660 --> 00:56:42.480
as to why women were only 3
to 5% of the top orchestras,

00:56:42.480 --> 00:56:44.140
and the maestro swore up

00:56:44.140 --> 00:56:45.910
and down "What are
you talking about?

00:56:45.910 --> 00:56:49.420
The only thing we care about
is the quality of the music."

00:56:49.420 --> 00:56:50.770
And the way it was resolved,

00:56:50.770 --> 00:56:54.200
that auditions would
be held behind screens

00:56:54.200 --> 00:56:56.980
and they even decided
to put a carpet

00:56:56.980 --> 00:56:59.050
down so you couldn't
tell whether it was a

00:56:59.050 --> 00:57:02.040
clup-clup-clup-clup of
high heels walking in

00:57:02.040 --> 00:57:06.010
or the soft sloughing of
loafers and what happened?

00:57:06.010 --> 00:57:08.590
Within 3 years, the
number of women

00:57:08.590 --> 00:57:11.520
in orchestras more than doubled.

00:57:11.520 --> 00:57:15.440
They're now up to 35% and
it's just a perfect example

00:57:15.440 --> 00:57:18.450
because it's an instance
where even more

00:57:18.450 --> 00:57:21.270
than evaluating legal work,

00:57:21.270 --> 00:57:24.120
these concert masters
were absolutely convinced

00:57:24.120 --> 00:57:27.630
under sodium pentothal that they
were reacting to nothing other

00:57:27.630 --> 00:57:32.040
than the quality of the music
and it's just a reminder

00:57:32.040 --> 00:57:35.500
that other things
infiltrate our decision-making

00:57:35.500 --> 00:57:38.340
that we're not even aware
of, and so for anybody

00:57:38.340 --> 00:57:42.250
who has 5 minutes today and
has not done, done it over,

00:57:42.250 --> 00:57:46.890
go take the implicit Bias Test;
harvardedu/implicitbiastest.

00:57:46.890 --> 00:57:48.770
It is free.

00:57:48.770 --> 00:57:50.480
It is confidential.

00:57:50.480 --> 00:57:54.150
You can test your own implicit
biases based on gender,

00:57:54.150 --> 00:58:00.070
ethnicity, religion, you can
even test your bias against age,

00:58:00.070 --> 00:58:04.490
obesity, it's remarkable,
because so many

00:58:04.490 --> 00:58:07.810
of us today really
believe we're colorblind,

00:58:07.810 --> 00:58:12.410
we're gender neutral, we're not
affected by this and, in fact,

00:58:12.410 --> 00:58:16.740
every study that's been done
shows that even at 6 months old,

00:58:16.740 --> 00:58:20.520
if you take babies and put
them in pink shirts and half

00:58:20.520 --> 00:58:25.030
of them are orange shirts, they
interact differently by virtue

00:58:25.030 --> 00:58:28.970
of the fact that they others
don't have the same color shirt.

00:58:28.970 --> 00:58:33.810
So, it's in our DNA that we
just make snap decisions based

00:58:33.810 --> 00:58:37.560
on appearances and that affects
our ability to be objective.

00:58:37.560 --> 00:58:39.330
So, take the test.

00:58:39.330 --> 00:58:41.050
You will be amazed.

00:58:41.050 --> 00:58:42.970
It's a real challenge not just

00:58:42.970 --> 00:58:45.060
for the law, but
across the board.

00:58:45.060 --> 00:58:47.170
How do we get past
our implicit biases,

00:58:47.170 --> 00:58:50.980
because it's affecting how
we elevate, compensate,

00:58:50.980 --> 00:58:55.750
and promote women, diverse
attorneys, and other people

00:58:55.750 --> 00:58:58.420
who don't look and
act like we do.

